      "content": "but wind and solar aren't a thing yet when it comes to massive industrial demand or if the sun isnt shining, right? it feels like people who don't want nuclear are just being unrealistic about the timeline we actually have. isn't it kind of a fact that renewables alone can't do the heavy lifting we need right now?",
